HEADWORD: Mastication
<hw>Mas`ti*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>masticatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>mastication</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
act or operation of masticating; chewing, as of food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Mastication</qex> is a necessary preparation of solid
aliment, without which there can be no good digestion.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masticator</ent>⟦br⟧
